{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"final","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"code":["        \/\/ Assuming in Figma with have a font semantic token typeDisplayLarge,","        \/\/ with values depending to size class. These values are defined as font composite raw tokens.","        let typeBold850 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize850, lineHeight: fontLineHeight1050, weight: fontWeight700, letterSpacing: fontLetterSpacing850)","        let typeBold1450 = FontCompositeRawToken(size: fontSize1450, lineHeight: fontLineHeight1850, weight: fontWeight700, letterSpacing: fontLetterSpacing1450)","","        \/\/ Then the develoment team declares an \"higher\" level font semantic token","        \/\/ inside FontCompositeSemanticTokens protocol,","        \/\/ and defined inside OUDSTheme+FontCompositeSemanticTokens extension","        var typeDisplayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens {","            MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(compact: FontRawTokens.typeBold850, regular: FontRawTokens.typeBold1450)","        }","","        \/\/ If the same font is used whatever the size class is","        var typeDisplayLarge: MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens { MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens(FontRawTokens.typeBold650) }","","        \/\/ The theme exposes both generated elevation semantic tokens and \"crafted\" higher level elevation semantic tokens.","        \/\/ It is recommended to use the higher level version as it is less error-prone."],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The case of this "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is quite particular because in fact it contains "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(i.e. raw tokens) instead of semantic tokens."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In fact there is not “font composite semantic tokens” defined in the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"Figma","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" kit."}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"0.8.0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Since"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Kind of semantic tokens which will wrap a combination of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FontCompositeRawToken"},{"type":"text","text":" depending to size classes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Kind of composite token with multiple values, but not named “composite” because this word is already used in the design system."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Allows to gather the multiple-value tokens from "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Figma"}]},{"type":"text","text":" inside one object."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If a font token exists with its value depending to the size class, it must be packed in such "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/documentation\/OUDSTokensSemantic\/MultipleFontCompositeRawTokens\/init(_:)","doc:\/\